{
  "stem": "16214.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Two and half years.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- basically I was actually for one year without my parents in Israel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because my-- as I've mentioned to you previously, my father really didn't want to be in Israel.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think the fact that the Israeli government took a lot of his-- basically earnings, I mean because my father brought from Poland everything, from BMW motorcycle, which he absolutely loved, to piano, to air conditioning, which they still didn't have, to refrigerator.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean I remember, I recall so well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because at the time, in 1956, when we got to Israel, the Israeli economy was still very poor.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And most of our relatives did not have all these luxuries yet.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And even, you know, my-- my mother's oldest-- eldest sister, Eva, whose husband was an architect, and he was doing quote, unquote 'very well,' they still did not have material goods, as many as we had that we brought from Poland.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But the [NON-ENGLISH]-- remember that, I still remember the word-- took almost half of what my parents brought in.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my father was very upset, very upset about it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Another thing is that he couldn't tolerate the very religious Jews who basically he said were running the country, yes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Which there's a little of truth to that, but not extensive truth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he just wanted to get out of there as soon as he possibly could.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Meantime, I was placed again, not against my-- I really didn't want to go to nursing school.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I was sort of told that this is where I'm going to go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that's it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, so I was placed in Hadassah, a Tel Aviv Nursing School, after I finished ulpan.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I started going to nursing school.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
